''Theorem.''
Consider a parameter-dependent dynamical system $$\dot{x} = f(x,\mu)$$ with $$f \in \smooth^1,$$ $$x \in \R^n,n \ge 2$$ and $$\mu \in \R.$$ Assume:

# $$x_0$$ is a fixed point at $$\mu = \mu_0.$$
# $$f'(x_0, \mu_0)$$ has maximal rank.
# $$\fracpartial{f}{x}(x_0, \mu_0)$$ has a pair of purely imaginary eigenvalues $$\lambda(\mu_0), \bar\lambda(\mu_0) \in i\R$$ and no further eigenvalues with $$\Re(\lambda_i) = 0.$$
# <div>Finally, assume that
$$
\left. \fracderiv{}{\mu} \right|_{\mu = \mu_0} \Re \lambda(\mu) \ne 0
$$
for the curve of Eigenvalues of $$\fracpartial{f}{x}(x(\mu),\mu).$$</div>

Then there exists a unique invariant 2-dimensional central manifold $$W^\mathrm{c}(\mu)$$ through $$x_0(\mu)$$ and a system of local coordinates $$(z_1, z_2)$$ on this manifold such that the dynamics there are described by
$$\begin{aligned}
\dot{z}_1 &= (d\mu + ar^2)z_1 - (w + c\mu + br^2)z_2 \\
\dot{z}_2 &= (w + c\mu + br^2)z_1 + (d\mu + ar^2)z_2,
\end{aligned}$$
with $$r^2 = z_1{}^2 + z_2{}^2$$ and certain constants $$a,b,c,d,w$$ depending on the vector field $$f.$$ If $$a \ne 0$$ then for small $$\mu$$ with $$\sign(\mu) = \sign(-d/a)$$ there exist [[limit cycles|Limit cycle]] on $$W^\mathrm{c}(\mu)$$ of the radius
$$
r \approx \sqrt{-\frac{d}{a} \mu}
$$
which are stable if $$a>0$$ and unstable if $$a<0.$$

